In a skillet, saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Add the apple, raisins, bouillon, salt, sage, poultry seasoning and pepper. Cook and stir 1-2 minutes longer. Stir in broth. Pour over bread crumbs; toss to coat. Transfer to a greased 1-qt. baking dish. Cover and bake at 350 degrees F for 25 minutes. Uncover; bake 20-25 minutes longer or until top is golden brown.